<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-14T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/2712: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="from">Sackett</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-14T10:00:00+01:00">April 14, 1932—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>75. Yesterday by emergency decree issued on unanimous recommendation
                                of the Cabinet the President disbanded all military Nazi
                                organizations, affecting allegedly over four hundred thousand
                                members. No serious disturbances have been reported as yet. It is
                                presumed that storm division will be re-formed in guise of sport
                                organization.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SFM1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Sackett</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>